It looks to me like you have a mistake in

    for (b = mergedHuffmanNodes; b &lt; distinctCharacterCount - 1 + i; b++){

in `sortHuffmanTree()`

because on the next line you do

    if (huffmanTreeNode[b].count &gt; huffmanTreeNode[b + 1].count){

where `b + 1` may be out of bounds.

